Implemented the controller in:

- `components/controller/controller.c`

Behavior now matches the task contract:

- boot defaults to safe off
- `LEVEL < 30` turns pump on
- `LEVEL > 80` turns pump off
- `30 <= LEVEL <= 80` holds prior actuator output
- malformed input forces safe off
- explicit timeout input forces safe off
- idle steps only time out after `> 1000 ms` since last valid sensor frame

Visible verification added in:

- `agent_tests/test_controller.py`

Checks cover every acceptance bullet plus an extra explicit `SENSOR_TIMEOUT` case, including a firmware UART end-to-end probe.

